Crack Surveillance Operatives have arrested three suspects over alleged possession and dealing of illicit drugs in Ofagbe Community, Isoko North Local Government Area of Delta State. The suspects include Alex Johnholt ‘m’ age 32yrs, Abe Ujiro ‘f’ age 25yrs and Omoro Joy ‘f’ age 26yrs. They were arrested during a raid of a criminal hideout in the Community by the Police. -Advertisement- The Police recovered from the suspects, one hundred and five {105} wraps of SK weeds, six {6} wraps of loud, sixteen {16} wraps of substance suspected to be cocaine, four {4} wraps of Indian hemp, four {4} litres of monkey tail, sixty {60} packs of razors and one Indian hemp grinding device. The Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali who confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe said,” the suspects will be arraigned in court as soon as the investigation is concluded.”